article.headline: Oral Roberts 84, Southern Utah 79
article.story: CEDAR CITY, Utah (AP) -- Caleb Green scored 33 points, including 23 in the second half, and had 13 rebounds in leading Oral Roberts to an 84-79 victory over Southern Utah Wednesday night. Larry Owens scored 21 points for the Golden Eagles (7-7, 2-0 Mid-Continent Conference), who led 63-52 with 10:22 to play but had to rally in the final 1:18 to win. Green's double-double was his fifth in the last six games and his eighth of the season. Lubor Olsovsky and Nate Janes scored 16 points each to lead Southern Utah (2-12, 1-1). Steve Barnes added 14 points for the Thunderbirds. Trailing 67-57 with 8:04 left, Southern Utah scored 11 straight points on Barnes 3-pointer from the right wing and consecutive layups by Olsovsky, Janes, Barnes and Justin Allen. The Thunderbirds led 74-71 on Barnes' jumper at 3:22 and 77-75 on a free throw by Janes at 1:35. Green sank a layup off the offensive board and was fouled by Olsovsky. His free throw gave the Eagles a 78-77 lead with 1:18 left. Owens, who scored 16 points in the second half, followed with a short jumper from right of the key, and Ken Tutt hit four straight free throws in the last 22 seconds. Oral Roberts shot 60 percent, including 72 percent in the second half. Southern Utah shot 59 percent in the second half after trailing 37-30 at halftime.
